1
00:00:00,240 --> 00:00:01,400
[Disclaimer:
All depicted events are fictional

2
00:00:01,440 --> 00:00:02,600
and for entertainment purposes only;
viewer discretion is advised]

3
00:00:55,360 --> 00:00:56,800
Do you remember that shop still?

4
00:00:58,240 --> 00:01:00,320
We should choose new rings to wear.

5
00:01:26,800 --> 00:01:27,880
Run! Now!

6
00:01:32,120 --> 00:01:33,120
Make way! Make way!

7
00:01:39,400 --> 00:01:40,240
Klao! Move!

8
00:01:41,880 --> 00:01:42,800
Klao! This way!

9
00:02:01,080 --> 00:02:02,560
We can go no further.

10
00:02:03,520 --> 00:02:04,760
You must hide here.

11
00:02:05,840 --> 00:02:06,960
I shall go and seize him myself.

12
00:02:08,039 --> 00:02:09,440
No, please!

13
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:11,880
What if we should be parted again?

14
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:13,880
Countless times have we been parted,

15
00:02:14,720 --> 00:02:16,320
yet ever do I find my way to you.

16
00:02:21,680 --> 00:02:22,840
I promise you,

17
00:02:24,680 --> 00:02:25,840
I shall return.

18
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:29,000
Nothing shall ever part us again.

19
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:10,600
[Love Upon a Time Series]

20
00:03:12,160 --> 00:03:14,200
Happy birthday, Nakun!

21
00:03:15,360 --> 00:03:20,320
[December 2023]

22
00:03:23,960 --> 00:03:24,800
Oh...

23
00:03:25,120 --> 00:03:26,120
We're so sorry.

24
00:03:44,520 --> 00:03:45,720
Gosh, Pun.

25
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:47,920
I thought Nakun was already at the shop?

26
00:03:48,360 --> 00:03:49,880
The surprise is ruined.

27
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:53,760
He really said he did,

28
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:56,079
but I have no idea why he's not here.

29
00:03:56,760 --> 00:03:57,560
That's okay.

30
00:03:57,800 --> 00:03:58,560
We'll try again.

31
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:01,440
Guys, do we still have any party poppers?

32
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:02,640
We're out.

33
00:04:03,040 --> 00:04:04,800
- He told me to pop them all at once.
- Oh...

34
00:04:06,760 --> 00:04:08,040
What do we do now?

35
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:09,280
Surprise.

36
00:04:27,160 --> 00:04:27,840
Damn.

37
00:04:28,400 --> 00:04:29,520
What the hell did you do?

38
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:31,600
I'm okay.

39
00:04:32,440 --> 00:04:33,280
I'm fine.

40
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:35,280
I'm alright!

41
00:04:42,080 --> 00:04:43,080
Damn!

42
00:04:43,659 --> 00:04:44,880
The state you're in...

43
00:04:45,080 --> 00:04:46,520
Why do you look so bad?

44
00:04:47,640 --> 00:04:48,520
Thee!

45
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:49,360
What?

46
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:51,000
Stop making fun of Nakun.

47
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:52,600
I'm not.

48
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:55,440
He's really forsaken by the heavens.

49
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:58,240
Taxis refused to take him,

50
00:04:58,600 --> 00:05:00,040
so he had to walk here.

51
00:05:00,320 --> 00:05:01,320
Then his umbrella broke,

52
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:03,360
and a motorcycle
splashed him as it drove by.

53
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:05,080
When he finally got here,

54
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:07,760
he even stepped in some mud.

55
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:09,440
Mhm...

56
00:05:10,360 --> 00:05:11,360
Bangkok...

57
00:05:12,160 --> 00:05:14,240
A city of life...

58
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:24,000
It's okay, buddy.

59
00:05:24,320 --> 00:05:25,480
Shake it off. Don't mind it.

60
00:05:26,280 --> 00:05:27,400
It's your birthday after all.

61
00:05:27,720 --> 00:05:28,920
Make a wish, buddy.

62
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:31,720
Mhm.

63
00:05:53,280 --> 00:05:54,600
Uh, Nakun...

64
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:04,360
Why do things always get in my way?

65
00:06:17,540 --> 00:06:19,040
Happy birthday, Nakun.

66
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:20,000
Thank you very much.

67
00:06:20,040 --> 00:06:21,760
Wishing you a ton of happiness.

68
00:06:22,960 --> 00:06:24,680
So have you...

69
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:26,080
made a wish again?

70
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:28,120
Yes, already.

71
00:06:28,280 --> 00:06:29,040
What did you wish for?

72
00:06:29,200 --> 00:06:30,360
Why do you want to know?

73
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:33,840
That way I'll know
if I should wish you well or not.

74
00:06:34,080 --> 00:06:36,400
Do you really have to choose
what kind of wish to give?

75
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:38,640
I want him to find a great partner

76
00:06:38,760 --> 00:06:39,960
so he's finally settled.

77
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:43,040
Better wish that for yourself.

78
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:45,720
I'm not officially taken,

79
00:06:46,320 --> 00:06:48,000
but I've already found myself a good love.

80
00:06:53,080 --> 00:06:54,080
Are you sure?

81
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:56,040
Of course I am.

82
00:06:56,920 --> 00:06:59,840
Even though you don't choose me now,

83
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:02,160
my love for you

84
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:04,600
is surely a good thing for you.

85
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:08,640
I need to use the toilet for a bit, Nakun.

86
00:07:09,320 --> 00:07:10,240
To relieve yourself?

87
00:07:11,480 --> 00:07:12,480
To throw up!

88
00:07:12,840 --> 00:07:13,520
Huh?

89
00:07:14,720 --> 00:07:16,560
Pun, I'll help you rub your back.

90
00:07:24,600 --> 00:07:26,720
[Mom]

91
00:07:37,159 --> 00:07:38,040
- I'll help.
- I'm so sorry.

92
00:07:38,320 --> 00:07:38,960
It's okay!

93
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:39,880
I'll help clean it up.

94
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:40,880
It's okay.

95
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:41,680
- It's fine.
- No, it's okay.

96
00:07:50,560 --> 00:07:51,720
Ow...

97
00:07:55,880 --> 00:07:56,880
Blood?!

98
00:07:58,600 --> 00:08:00,080
Shit! My phone!

99
00:08:02,040 --> 00:08:03,280
The screen's totally cracked!

100
00:08:03,680 --> 00:08:05,960
Shit!!

101
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:20,720
So damn unlucky.

102
00:08:22,600 --> 00:08:23,960
Can it be fixed, Nakun?

103
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:25,480
You'd be better off getting a new one.

104
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:27,040
I can't.

105
00:08:27,280 --> 00:08:29,240
No modeling gigs are coming up.

106
00:08:30,260 --> 00:08:31,360
I do think I'm handsome, though...

107
00:08:33,520 --> 00:08:34,480
- Whoa!
- Whoa!

108
00:08:34,679 --> 00:08:35,480
- Bird poop!
- Nakun...

109
00:08:35,520 --> 00:08:36,720
A bird pooped on your head!

110
00:08:36,880 --> 00:08:37,679
Nakun!

111
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:39,240
- Oh, that's a lot.
- Give me a moment.

112
00:08:39,480 --> 00:08:40,720
- Pun, wipe it off my head!
- Whoa...

113
00:08:44,920 --> 00:08:46,400
Get it off my head!

114
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:48,760
- Pun, please wipe it off my head!
- Whoa!

115
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:50,240
- Get it off!
- I'm on it. Please wait.

116
00:08:58,240 --> 00:08:59,760
How can someone be this unlucky?

117
00:09:00,440 --> 00:09:02,080
Gosh, you're so unlucky!

118
00:09:02,880 --> 00:09:03,960
At least it's gone.

119
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:06,720
- Not like this!
- Just as you requested.

120
00:09:19,560 --> 00:09:22,560
[One month later]

121
00:09:27,480 --> 00:09:29,160
♫Let's skinship♫

122
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:30,880
♫This is freaking drip♫

123
00:09:31,040 --> 00:09:32,560
♫Moving closer♫

124
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:34,360
♫I'll whisper you with my feelings♫

125
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:36,200
♫Just skinship♫

126
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:37,800
♫My heart's in heat♫

127
00:09:37,840 --> 00:09:39,560
♫Blowing you a kiss♫

128
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:41,080
♫With no rehearsal needed♫

129
00:09:41,120 --> 00:09:42,800
♫Love is nothing you can touch♫

130
00:09:42,840 --> 00:09:44,520
♫No measurement can hold this much♫

131
00:09:44,560 --> 00:09:46,240
♫Let be clear, make it all clean-cut♫

132
00:09:46,280 --> 00:09:47,560
♫It's the feeling,♫

133
00:09:49,350 --> 00:09:50,700
Help me! Somebody!

134
00:09:50,740 --> 00:09:52,740
Help! Someone just stole my handbag!

135
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:55,600
Help me!

136
00:09:56,360 --> 00:09:57,480
Please help!

137
00:09:57,680 --> 00:09:59,800
That guy over there!
Help me catch the thief, please!

138
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:00,920
- Help me, please!
- Sure.

139
00:10:01,480 --> 00:10:02,720
Please! Catch that guy!

140
00:10:06,880 --> 00:10:07,680
Stop!

141
00:10:09,760 --> 00:10:11,880
- Stop!
- Somebody, please catch the thief!

142
00:10:11,920 --> 00:10:13,120
Catch him, please!

143
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:14,600
Hey, stop!

144
00:10:23,620 --> 00:10:24,720
Stop running away already!

145
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:27,840
Hey!

146
00:10:29,520 --> 00:10:30,360
Let go.

147
00:10:31,280 --> 00:10:32,920
You're a thief, yet you're so slow.

148
00:10:35,280 --> 00:10:36,680
Give the handbag back to her.

149
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:38,760
If she takes this up,

150
00:10:39,140 --> 00:10:40,840
you'll end up in jail
and get a criminal record!

151
00:10:41,120 --> 00:10:42,240
Hey, man...

152
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:43,880
What do you want from me?

153
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:45,560
Please let me go.

154
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:47,400
My mom's sick.

155
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:49,520
This money's for her.

156
00:10:51,360 --> 00:10:52,520
Listen to me.

157
00:10:54,140 --> 00:10:56,080
To be human is to fight.

158
00:10:58,240 --> 00:10:59,520
But don't fight others.

159
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:02,720
You're still young

160
00:11:04,800 --> 00:11:05,960
with a bright future ahead.

161
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:09,400
It's not too late to change your mind.

162
00:11:10,480 --> 00:11:11,440
It's that person.

163
00:11:11,480 --> 00:11:12,400
- It's that guy!
- Stop!

164
00:11:12,440 --> 00:11:13,600
- What the hell?
- Stop!!

165
00:11:13,640 --> 00:11:14,560
- That's my handbag.
- Hey!

166
00:11:14,880 --> 00:11:15,800
That's mine.

167
00:11:16,220 --> 00:11:17,800
You're a thief, yet you're so slow.

168
00:11:18,040 --> 00:11:19,040
If she takes this up,

169
00:11:19,280 --> 00:11:21,160
you'll end up in jail
and get a criminal record.

170
00:11:22,960 --> 00:11:24,360
Please listen to me.

171
00:11:24,640 --> 00:11:25,360
So...

172
00:11:25,600 --> 00:11:27,840
To be human is to fight.

173
00:11:28,640 --> 00:11:29,720
But don't fight me.

174
00:11:30,760 --> 00:11:32,040
Guys, listen to me.

175
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:33,080
I fucking... Sorry.

176
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:34,400
I didn't...

177
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:40,000
Just believe me.

178
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,720
I think it's getting worse and worse.

179
00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:44,320
This isn't normal.

180
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:46,080
So what?

181
00:11:46,280 --> 00:11:47,880
You're acting like I can change anything.

182
00:11:48,080 --> 00:11:49,200
Of course you can.

183
00:11:49,240 --> 00:11:50,680
That's why I brought you here.

184
00:11:58,440 --> 00:12:01,040
[Fortune Teller Rattikarn's Pavilion]

185
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:04,080
Are you crazy?

186
00:12:04,740 --> 00:12:05,520
No thanks.

187
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:06,400
I'm leaving.

188
00:12:06,440 --> 00:12:07,480
Hold on!

189
00:12:07,520 --> 00:12:09,400
The fortune teller here is really good.

190
00:12:09,680 --> 00:12:10,800
Take my mom's word for it.

191
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:12,480
If it doesn't work out,

192
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,200
you can just go home,

193
00:12:14,320 --> 00:12:15,120
okay?

194
00:12:21,320 --> 00:12:22,680
Give it a try, Nakun.

195
00:12:23,840 --> 00:12:25,720
If this is a scam, we'll leave.

196
00:12:29,520 --> 00:12:31,280
Things like this are always a scam.

197
00:12:42,520 --> 00:12:43,440
Do you believe me now?

198
00:12:43,760 --> 00:12:44,880
This is the real deal.

199
00:12:47,540 --> 00:12:48,320
No.

200
00:12:48,480 --> 00:12:49,760
No matter how bad things get,

201
00:12:49,800 --> 00:12:50,720
I'll never...

202
00:12:54,360 --> 00:12:55,720
So cold!

203
00:12:57,800 --> 00:13:00,240
How many times do I have to get soaked?

204
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:04,920
Come on, the water is warm.

205
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:07,000
I don't buy it.

206
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:09,000
You forced me here,
and now you're mocking me?

207
00:13:12,640 --> 00:13:13,880
The water really is warm, Nakun.

208
00:13:13,920 --> 00:13:14,640
It's hot, even.

209
00:13:16,080 --> 00:13:17,480
One misfortune after another.

210
00:13:18,160 --> 00:13:20,080
If holy water makes you shiver,

211
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:21,640
then it's no surprise.

212
00:13:24,100 --> 00:13:25,300
Ow!

213
00:13:30,700 --> 00:13:31,920
Once you get changed,

214
00:13:32,280 --> 00:13:33,440
head inside.

215
00:13:34,300 --> 00:13:36,000
We have a lot to talk about.

216
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:44,800
Hey.

217
00:13:46,680 --> 00:13:50,400
How did you like the warm bath service?

218
00:13:50,510 --> 00:13:52,000
- Come and try it yourself.
- Whoa, whoa!

219
00:13:52,040 --> 00:13:52,880
Wait, wait.

220
00:13:54,640 --> 00:13:55,280
- Out of the way!
- Whoa...

221
00:13:55,320 --> 00:13:57,800
- Looking good, Nakun.
- That's enough, Thee.

222
00:13:58,360 --> 00:13:59,240
Move.

223
00:13:59,640 --> 00:14:00,720
Hey, what the hell?

224
00:14:01,040 --> 00:14:02,280
Wait up, please!

225
00:14:14,720 --> 00:14:15,800
Don't leave just yet.

226
00:14:21,560 --> 00:14:22,640
What the hell is wrong with you?

227
00:14:31,520 --> 00:14:33,360
Rahu transits the natal sign.

228
00:14:33,400 --> 00:14:35,200
You are about to experience misfortune.

229
00:14:36,320 --> 00:14:37,120
And?

230
00:14:38,960 --> 00:14:40,320
An incident will occur...

231
00:14:40,680 --> 00:14:41,480
No.

232
00:14:41,920 --> 00:14:43,120
It has already occurred

233
00:14:44,040 --> 00:14:45,520
since your birthday last month.

234
00:14:45,560 --> 00:14:46,320
Whoa...

235
00:14:46,760 --> 00:14:47,840
How did she know?

236
00:14:49,470 --> 00:14:50,800
It's all written right here,
[4 December 2003]

237
00:14:50,840 --> 00:14:53,000
his date of birth and everything.

238
00:14:53,040 --> 00:14:54,040
We've already told her everything.

239
00:14:54,080 --> 00:14:55,080
At any rate...

240
00:14:55,680 --> 00:14:58,280
The reading I did was from his natal chart.

241
00:14:59,080 --> 00:15:00,200
I truly mean well.

242
00:15:01,040 --> 00:15:03,480
This misfortune is fatal.

243
00:15:05,520 --> 00:15:06,600
Be extremely careful.

244
00:15:08,680 --> 00:15:09,640
I'm heading home.

245
00:15:16,400 --> 00:15:18,000
What promise did you make, and to whom?

246
00:15:18,680 --> 00:15:20,160
Someone from the past
awaits its fulfillment.

247
00:15:23,120 --> 00:15:23,920
Whoa, this is giving me chills.

248
00:15:24,040 --> 00:15:25,160
Who did you make a promise to?

249
00:15:25,780 --> 00:15:27,360
None. This is nonsense.

250
00:15:27,920 --> 00:15:30,080
Nakun, this is a serious matter.

251
00:15:30,120 --> 00:15:31,320
If it is, then why are you smiling?

252
00:15:33,480 --> 00:15:35,880
Is there any way we can help him?

253
00:15:37,120 --> 00:15:38,080
Hold him down!

254
00:15:38,120 --> 00:15:39,640
- Let me go!
- Hey! Hey!

255
00:15:39,760 --> 00:15:41,160
- Thee, let me go!
- Pun, help me out!

256
00:15:42,320 --> 00:15:43,280
I don't want to!

257
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:45,600
- Pun, help me!
- Let me go!

258
00:15:45,860 --> 00:15:47,200
Thee, don't!

259
00:15:47,240 --> 00:15:48,200
Thee!

260
00:15:48,460 --> 00:15:50,080
I told you to let me go!!

261
00:15:50,120 --> 00:15:51,120
Quite a fighter, aren't you?!

262
00:16:15,520 --> 00:16:16,560
Thanks.

263
00:16:22,120 --> 00:16:22,960
As for you...

264
00:16:24,280 --> 00:16:26,120
it might be wise
to lift the curse you made long ago.

265
00:16:26,880 --> 00:16:27,760
Me?

266
00:16:28,140 --> 00:16:29,840
Whoever you felt resentment toward,

267
00:16:30,640 --> 00:16:31,960
release the grudges you hold.

268
00:16:32,260 --> 00:16:33,740
This will break the cycle.

269
00:16:36,280 --> 00:16:37,200
And you...

270
00:16:38,360 --> 00:16:39,760
Visit your family if possible.

271
00:16:40,480 --> 00:16:42,080
Pray for and take care of your mom and dad.

272
00:16:42,520 --> 00:16:44,160
This will alleviate your misfortune.

273
00:16:44,960 --> 00:16:46,080
I don't have a dad.

274
00:16:46,480 --> 00:16:47,480
It's just a divorce.

275
00:16:48,360 --> 00:16:50,040
He didn't pass away or anything.

276
00:16:51,080 --> 00:16:52,520
He is still your father.

277
00:16:56,880 --> 00:16:58,080
And...

278
00:16:59,960 --> 00:17:01,720
you're going back to Ayutthaya anyway,
aren't you?

279
00:17:03,040 --> 00:17:03,960
Did you tell her that?

280
00:17:04,319 --> 00:17:05,680
No, I didn't.

281
00:17:05,720 --> 00:17:07,119
I have no idea what you're thinking.

282
00:17:10,280 --> 00:17:11,800
I don't need to be told that.

283
00:17:12,319 --> 00:17:13,680
This Friday,

284
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:15,440
your mom is going to call you.

285
00:17:16,480 --> 00:17:19,680
At night,
don't forget to bathe in the moonlight.

286
00:17:20,480 --> 00:17:21,599
And wear this.

287
00:17:22,040 --> 00:17:23,400
No, I'm not wearing it.

288
00:17:24,440 --> 00:17:26,000
Hey, Thee!

289
00:17:27,319 --> 00:17:28,840
You must not take it off.

290
00:17:35,200 --> 00:17:36,480
It's no use trying.

291
00:17:39,300 --> 00:17:40,300
Keep it on.

292
00:17:47,480 --> 00:17:48,800
Time travel literature

293
00:17:48,840 --> 00:17:51,560
is not just about traveling into the future

294
00:17:51,920 --> 00:17:55,040
or back in time to change something.

295
00:17:55,420 --> 00:17:58,800
It questions whether time itself

296
00:17:58,960 --> 00:18:02,640
is a phenomenon of nature
[How is this important to me?]

297
00:18:02,680 --> 00:18:05,400
or merely an illusion created by humans.

298
00:18:07,440 --> 00:18:13,520
We may think time moves linearly,

299
00:18:13,560 --> 00:18:16,120
but in the world of time travel literature,

300
00:18:17,100 --> 00:18:20,500
it is often portrayed as fragmented.

301
00:18:23,560 --> 00:18:26,240
It jumps back and forth,

302
00:18:26,280 --> 00:18:27,720
moving in circles,

303
00:18:28,660 --> 00:18:30,660
as if it were a dream

304
00:18:30,960 --> 00:18:33,160
or a memory.

305
00:18:34,440 --> 00:18:37,040
- It loops back,
- Why are you taking notes in English?

306
00:18:37,520 --> 00:18:39,360
- becoming a cycle.
- I was just going to ask for it.

307
00:18:39,760 --> 00:18:41,080
This suggests that

308
00:18:41,600 --> 00:18:43,800
the concepts of past and future lives
might actually exist.

309
00:18:48,800 --> 00:18:50,080
Thee, give it back to me.

310
00:18:52,640 --> 00:18:53,920
Students over there...

311
00:18:57,680 --> 00:18:58,480
Yes, you.

312
00:19:02,740 --> 00:19:03,840
What's your name?

313
00:19:04,840 --> 00:19:05,560
She's asking you...

314
00:19:15,360 --> 00:19:16,040
Uh...

315
00:19:16,720 --> 00:19:18,440
It's Kun,

316
00:19:20,440 --> 00:19:22,800
short for Nakun.

317
00:19:23,040 --> 00:19:24,320
"Kun, short for Nakun?"

318
00:19:25,160 --> 00:19:27,640
That's a mouthful.

319
00:19:29,760 --> 00:19:33,160
You can call me Kun for short, Professor.

320
00:19:41,160 --> 00:19:43,360
Do you believe in multiple lifetimes?

321
00:19:44,760 --> 00:19:46,240
Yeah, do you?

322
00:19:46,600 --> 00:19:47,400
Answer her.

323
00:19:47,720 --> 00:19:48,520
Do you?

324
00:19:49,080 --> 00:19:49,840
Come on.

325
00:19:51,320 --> 00:19:52,160
Answer the question.

326
00:19:52,560 --> 00:19:53,440
I don't.

327
00:19:58,200 --> 00:20:03,000
I think it's an idea created by humans

328
00:20:03,640 --> 00:20:05,560
to cope with loss

329
00:20:07,080 --> 00:20:09,440
or things they can't explain.

330
00:20:11,360 --> 00:20:12,400
Interesting.

331
00:20:12,560 --> 00:20:13,560
And?

332
00:20:13,960 --> 00:20:14,680
Well...

333
00:20:15,600 --> 00:20:17,440
Say, if we were born with hardships,

334
00:20:18,960 --> 00:20:22,120
we might say it's the consequence
of actions from a past life.

335
00:20:23,080 --> 00:20:24,920
We'd then tell ourselves to be content
with what we have

336
00:20:25,480 --> 00:20:28,520
and to keep cultivating good deeds,

337
00:20:30,240 --> 00:20:33,160
without recognizing
the underlying social issues.

338
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:34,600
Sheesh.

339
00:20:37,840 --> 00:20:40,200
I believe in logic.

340
00:20:41,020 --> 00:20:42,600
Every action

341
00:20:42,640 --> 00:20:44,320
has its consequences.

342
00:20:45,040 --> 00:20:46,040
But...

343
00:20:46,480 --> 00:20:49,720
I don't think consequences
carry over to our next lives.

344
00:20:51,360 --> 00:20:53,160
What an interesting answer.

345
00:20:53,640 --> 00:20:57,760
Those who don't believe in
multiple lifetimes might think that

346
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:02,640
we have the power to shape our own destiny

347
00:21:03,120 --> 00:21:06,120
and that nothing is predetermined,

348
00:21:06,480 --> 00:21:07,360
correct?

349
00:21:10,520 --> 00:21:11,640
Be careful, Nakun.

350
00:21:13,080 --> 00:21:16,000
In the world of time travel literature,

351
00:21:16,440 --> 00:21:20,200
we cannot always rely on logic.

352
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:27,880
It might reflect something
that lies deep within.

353
00:21:28,400 --> 00:21:31,600
It might be fear,

354
00:21:33,520 --> 00:21:34,640
hope,

355
00:21:35,200 --> 00:21:40,000
or the unwillingness
to believe in something,

356
00:21:40,760 --> 00:21:41,640
correct?

357
00:21:43,520 --> 00:21:44,520
Well, I...

358
00:21:45,160 --> 00:21:46,560
I have no fear, Professor.

359
00:21:50,800 --> 00:21:52,520
You have no fear?

360
00:21:53,160 --> 00:21:56,080
Be honest with yourself and ask

361
00:21:57,160 --> 00:21:59,960
whether you truly have no fear.

362
00:22:13,400 --> 00:22:14,120
Hey.

363
00:22:14,360 --> 00:22:15,160
Come on.

364
00:22:15,760 --> 00:22:16,600
Take it easy.

365
00:22:17,360 --> 00:22:18,200
You better sit down.

366
00:22:36,440 --> 00:22:38,080
Do you believe in multiple lifetimes?'

367
00:22:38,880 --> 00:22:40,960
That's the topic of your assignment.

368
00:22:41,360 --> 00:22:43,680
- Oh...
- Gosh!

369
00:22:43,720 --> 00:22:45,040
The deadline is today.

370
00:22:45,160 --> 00:22:47,360
No!

371
00:22:48,240 --> 00:22:49,440
Class dismissed.

372
00:22:50,560 --> 00:22:51,400
Nakun.

373
00:22:51,760 --> 00:22:54,480
Go take care of your Mother,
as the fortune teller said.

374
00:22:55,440 --> 00:22:56,440
Having ill luck is bad enough,

375
00:22:56,480 --> 00:22:57,800
yet you have doomed us all.

376
00:22:58,860 --> 00:23:00,240
That has nothing to do with me.

377
00:23:00,560 --> 00:23:02,800
Professors here love giving
piles of assignments.

378
00:23:05,040 --> 00:23:07,040
Why the hell
do I have to get into this faculty?

379
00:23:10,520 --> 00:23:12,400
Can we go back in time and change this?

380
00:23:13,800 --> 00:23:14,720
Going back in time?

381
00:23:15,340 --> 00:23:16,280
See?

382
00:23:16,800 --> 00:23:18,800
The professor has stuffed your head
with ideas about time travel.

383
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:21,280
Yeah, you're right.

384
00:23:22,920 --> 00:23:23,920
But I'd rather not.

385
00:23:24,200 --> 00:23:25,560
If I studied at a different faculty,

386
00:23:25,600 --> 00:23:27,200
I wouldn't get to see Pun.

387
00:23:28,400 --> 00:23:29,560
Has anyone ever told you that

388
00:23:30,520 --> 00:23:32,240
when you talk about Pun,

389
00:23:32,960 --> 00:23:34,560
you act like a Siberian Husky?

390
00:23:37,040 --> 00:23:37,720
Who said that?

391
00:23:38,240 --> 00:23:39,240
Was it Pun?

392
00:23:39,440 --> 00:23:40,120
Me.

393
00:23:41,940 --> 00:23:45,680
Pun is like a Persian cat, though.

394
00:23:46,260 --> 00:23:48,920
Cats and dogs don't get along very well.

395
00:23:50,760 --> 00:23:52,080
Wait, but I've seen videos on TikTok.

396
00:23:52,120 --> 00:23:53,480
They can be together, alright?

397
00:23:54,200 --> 00:23:55,760
Stop talking nonsense.

398
00:23:59,040 --> 00:24:00,440
Yeah, what does this mean?

399
00:24:01,400 --> 00:24:02,400
Nakun...

400
00:24:02,700 --> 00:24:03,440
Nakun.

401
00:24:03,840 --> 00:24:04,640
Nakun!

402
00:24:08,200 --> 00:24:09,440
I'm here to return your notes.

403
00:24:09,680 --> 00:24:10,960
Thanks to you,

404
00:24:11,000 --> 00:24:13,120
I got the top score
in the Western History midterm exam.

405
00:24:13,480 --> 00:24:14,240
Thank you.

406
00:24:14,560 --> 00:24:16,080
Whoa, you're amazing, Pun.

407
00:24:16,280 --> 00:24:18,480
Your fraternity brother
topped the class in English, you know?

408
00:24:19,040 --> 00:24:21,000
But he's a goner
when it comes to Thai History.

409
00:24:21,320 --> 00:24:21,960
Huh?

410
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:22,920
Thee.

411
00:24:23,220 --> 00:24:25,280
What? The midterm exam was last week,

412
00:24:25,480 --> 00:24:27,280
and you said
you couldn't remember a thing.

413
00:24:27,760 --> 00:24:30,040
We're talking about Nakun here, you know?

414
00:24:30,340 --> 00:24:31,560
He was just being humble, more like.

415
00:24:31,680 --> 00:24:33,560
He'll get an A when the results come out.

416
00:24:34,040 --> 00:24:35,040
Yeah, you're right.

417
00:24:35,520 --> 00:24:37,320
Nakun always tells us he hasn't studied

418
00:24:37,500 --> 00:24:38,320
and can't do the exam,

419
00:24:38,360 --> 00:24:40,080
but he always
ends up at the top of the class.

420
00:24:40,480 --> 00:24:41,200
Mhm.

421
00:24:45,080 --> 00:24:46,680
[Mom]

422
00:24:46,800 --> 00:24:49,440
Nakun, are you coming home
for the break?

423
00:24:49,480 --> 00:24:50,720
I miss you.

424
00:24:50,760 --> 00:24:52,560
We haven't celebrated your birthday.

425
00:24:52,600 --> 00:24:54,640
Give me a call once your classes are over.

426
00:24:56,760 --> 00:24:59,080
By the way, Pun,
we studied time travel literature today.

427
00:24:59,440 --> 00:25:00,840
The topic was about multiple lifetimes.

428
00:25:02,280 --> 00:25:04,640
- Do you believe in stuff like that?
- Multiple lifetimes.

429
00:25:05,920 --> 00:25:06,920
Um...

430
00:25:07,520 --> 00:25:08,520
I guess I do.

431
00:25:08,720 --> 00:25:11,560
The concept sounds fun
if you think about it.

432
00:25:12,040 --> 00:25:13,880
If you do, I will too.

433
00:25:14,520 --> 00:25:17,720
Perhaps our paths
might have crossed in past lives.

434
00:25:18,560 --> 00:25:20,080
Then, we'll meet again in the next one.

435
00:25:20,520 --> 00:25:21,360
Okay.

436
00:25:22,440 --> 00:25:23,440
Then, I don't believe in it.

437
00:25:24,040 --> 00:25:25,840
This lifetime is more than enough.

438
00:25:26,640 --> 00:25:28,640
What? Why?

439
00:25:29,280 --> 00:25:31,760
There are only
so many lifetimes for souls to meet, Thee.

440
00:25:31,800 --> 00:25:33,200
Can't I just meet you again
in the next life?

441
00:25:33,240 --> 00:25:34,840
This lifetime is already killing me.

442
00:25:35,040 --> 00:25:35,800
Why?

443
00:25:35,840 --> 00:25:37,040
- No.
- Pun, wait up!

444
00:25:37,080 --> 00:25:38,360
- Nope.
- What's the rush?

445
00:25:38,400 --> 00:25:40,800
- Why are you always on my case?
- Come on, wait for me.

446
00:26:07,360 --> 00:26:08,560
Be careful, Nakun.

447
00:26:09,900 --> 00:26:13,160
In the world of time travel literature,

448
00:26:13,200 --> 00:26:17,000
we cannot always rely on logic.

449
00:26:17,880 --> 00:26:24,040
It might reflect something
that lies deep within.

450
00:26:32,440 --> 00:26:33,640
Be careful, Nakun.

451
00:26:36,320 --> 00:26:37,160
Hey! Nakun!

452
00:26:37,200 --> 00:26:38,000
Nakun!

453
00:26:40,200 --> 00:26:41,800
[D.E. 6613,
Phra Nakhon Si Ayutthaya]

454
00:26:42,240 --> 00:26:43,960
Are you okay? All good?

455
00:26:45,040 --> 00:26:46,040
I'm okay.

456
00:26:46,520 --> 00:26:47,480
I'm fine.

457
00:26:47,880 --> 00:26:48,880
It's okay.

458
00:26:50,080 --> 00:26:51,080
That really scared me.

459
00:27:04,240 --> 00:27:05,080
Whoa...

460
00:27:05,360 --> 00:27:06,520
Hey, Nakun.

461
00:27:06,640 --> 00:27:07,320
Nakun!

462
00:27:07,360 --> 00:27:08,200
- Nakun! Look out!
- Hey!

463
00:27:14,400 --> 00:27:15,080
Hey...

464
00:27:15,560 --> 00:27:16,560
- Shit...
- Nakun!

465
00:27:18,280 --> 00:27:19,160
Are you hurt?

466
00:27:19,320 --> 00:27:20,040
Damn...

467
00:27:21,760 --> 00:27:22,920
How did that fall over?

468
00:27:23,820 --> 00:27:24,920
Are you okay?

469
00:27:25,600 --> 00:27:26,720
Are you alright, Nakun?

470
00:27:30,000 --> 00:27:31,200
You're...

471
00:27:32,280 --> 00:27:34,040
going back to Ayutthaya anyway,
aren't you?

472
00:27:34,480 --> 00:27:35,800
It just fell down randomly.

473
00:27:36,280 --> 00:27:38,880
[D.E. 6613,
Phra Nakhon Si Ayutthaya]

474
00:27:46,400 --> 00:27:47,200
Mom...

475
00:27:58,520 --> 00:28:00,600
[Certificate of Excellence]
[Master Nakun Phattanatada]

476
00:28:13,760 --> 00:28:15,240
I'm finally home.

477
00:28:35,120 --> 00:28:36,120
Oh, Nakun?

478
00:28:36,400 --> 00:28:37,560
You're home late.

479
00:28:38,320 --> 00:28:39,520
Oh, Mom?

480
00:28:53,520 --> 00:28:54,880
Whoa...

481
00:28:55,520 --> 00:28:57,640
You look amazing, Ma'am.

482
00:28:58,160 --> 00:29:00,360
Your son just got home,
and you're leaving already?

483
00:29:00,800 --> 00:29:02,380
Oh no, I'm not.

484
00:29:02,420 --> 00:29:04,600
I'm leaving for
the District Chief's child's wedding.

485
00:29:05,080 --> 00:29:06,640
Do you want to come with me?

486
00:29:06,800 --> 00:29:08,360
The party will last
the whole night, you know?

487
00:29:08,720 --> 00:29:09,720
I'll call it a pass.

488
00:29:10,000 --> 00:29:11,200
District Chief's child?

489
00:29:11,600 --> 00:29:12,840
I don't even know the name.

490
00:29:14,560 --> 00:29:15,560
I thought so.

491
00:29:16,440 --> 00:29:20,600
But I've prepared dinner for you.

492
00:29:21,640 --> 00:29:23,000
Eat a lot of rice, alright?

493
00:29:23,040 --> 00:29:24,120
Don't just go for the main dishes.

494
00:29:25,760 --> 00:29:26,640
Mhm...

495
00:29:30,600 --> 00:29:31,720
Whoa!

496
00:29:32,240 --> 00:29:33,600
This much?

497
00:29:34,120 --> 00:29:35,860
Are you throwing a party or something?

498
00:29:36,560 --> 00:29:37,720
You'll finish all of that.

499
00:29:38,200 --> 00:29:39,960
Oh, if you're not full,

500
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:44,920
there are fruits and snacks in the fridge.

501
00:29:44,960 --> 00:29:47,040
Go ahead and go to town on them, got it?

502
00:29:47,200 --> 00:29:48,200
Sure...

503
00:29:49,440 --> 00:29:50,240
Do I look beautiful now?

504
00:29:52,960 --> 00:29:54,000
I guess.

505
00:29:54,680 --> 00:29:56,400
I'll be going now.

506
00:30:02,520 --> 00:30:03,200
Nakun!

507
00:30:03,960 --> 00:30:04,640
Wait...

508
00:30:05,200 --> 00:30:06,760
What happened to your face?!

509
00:30:07,400 --> 00:30:08,280
Huh?

510
00:30:09,440 --> 00:30:11,160
Oh, this?

511
00:30:12,720 --> 00:30:14,960
No one would dare hurt me, Mom.

512
00:30:15,720 --> 00:30:18,160
I fell over.

513
00:30:18,320 --> 00:30:20,720
And I ended up slamming my head!

514
00:30:20,840 --> 00:30:22,960
So my face got all swollen...

515
00:30:26,360 --> 00:30:27,440
Oh, for goodness' sake...

516
00:30:27,560 --> 00:30:30,000
So you were just being clumsy as usual.

517
00:30:30,320 --> 00:30:33,520
I thought you got into a fight
or something.

518
00:30:35,120 --> 00:30:37,280
Who would I even fight, Mom?

519
00:30:37,880 --> 00:30:41,360
You, the deputy,
have taught me since I was little

520
00:30:41,400 --> 00:30:43,200
that violence is off-limits.

521
00:30:44,600 --> 00:30:47,640
And when I do something,
make sure no one can criticize me.

522
00:30:47,680 --> 00:30:48,920
Isn't that right?

523
00:30:50,240 --> 00:30:52,080
I'm so proud of you, honey.

524
00:30:52,120 --> 00:30:53,280
That really warms my heart.

525
00:30:53,640 --> 00:30:55,240
Gosh! What's gotten into you?

526
00:30:55,480 --> 00:30:56,800
I'm overjoyed, okay?

527
00:30:56,840 --> 00:30:57,960
I'm proud of you.

528
00:30:58,000 --> 00:31:01,240
Raising you on my own
into the good boy you are today

529
00:31:01,280 --> 00:31:02,180
makes me incredibly proud.

530
00:31:02,220 --> 00:31:03,100
One more.

531
00:31:06,680 --> 00:31:08,000
What is this?

532
00:31:09,840 --> 00:31:11,160
Why don't you head out already?

533
00:31:11,520 --> 00:31:12,960
Drinks don't pour themselves, you know.

534
00:31:14,360 --> 00:31:15,560
I don't drink.

535
00:31:17,880 --> 00:31:18,680
I'm off.

536
00:31:22,080 --> 00:31:23,080
Good luck.

537
00:31:23,640 --> 00:31:24,640
Thanks!

538
00:31:40,480 --> 00:31:41,680
And you said you don't drink...

539
00:31:46,480 --> 00:31:47,480
Well then...

540
00:31:48,400 --> 00:31:49,680
If she doesn't drink,

541
00:31:52,440 --> 00:31:53,640
this is all mine.

542
00:31:57,600 --> 00:31:59,840
[Detective Conan]

543
00:32:25,760 --> 00:32:27,120
[Do you believe in multiple lifetimes?]

544
00:32:27,160 --> 00:32:28,520
[I freaking don't!]

545
00:32:41,360 --> 00:32:43,680
"Thai History Test Results."

546
00:32:44,480 --> 00:32:46,360
What?
Why did the results come out so early?

547
00:32:48,520 --> 00:32:50,450
"Mr. Nakun Pattanatada"

548
00:32:52,120 --> 00:32:53,640
I got...

549
00:32:53,680 --> 00:32:56,680
14.5?

550
00:33:18,380 --> 00:33:20,380
First time failing an exam.

551
00:33:22,040 --> 00:33:23,840
Am I really suffering from misfortune?

552
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:42,800
Geese.

553
00:33:43,000 --> 00:33:44,000
Geese, where are you guys?

554
00:33:45,760 --> 00:33:46,640
Geese!

555
00:33:47,720 --> 00:33:49,560
Come out, it's feeding time.

556
00:33:50,800 --> 00:33:51,920
Where are they?

557
00:33:59,930 --> 00:34:01,170
Oh, I missed the bucket.

558
00:34:04,040 --> 00:34:05,160
Come and feed yourselves, then.

559
00:34:12,440 --> 00:34:13,800
It's always me!

560
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:16,120
It always happens to me!

561
00:34:17,900 --> 00:34:21,760
Why does a future honor English student
have to fail Thai History?!

562
00:34:22,880 --> 00:34:24,520
If past lives do exist,

563
00:34:24,800 --> 00:34:26,920
why aren't my past memories
carried over into this life

564
00:34:27,360 --> 00:34:29,679
so I don't have to study Thai History?!

565
00:34:29,960 --> 00:34:30,760
Gosh!

566
00:34:34,639 --> 00:34:35,719
Might as well take a swig...

567
00:34:48,920 --> 00:34:50,000
Gorgeous.

568
00:34:53,719 --> 00:34:54,560
Look...

569
00:34:54,920 --> 00:34:56,719
Even a star is falling on me.

570
00:35:07,920 --> 00:35:08,880
Is it actually falling?

571
00:35:30,240 --> 00:35:31,280
Ow...

572
00:35:48,000 --> 00:35:49,120
Master Klao is over there!

573
00:35:50,480 --> 00:35:52,240
Tread lightly!
There are king cobra dens.

574
00:35:56,160 --> 00:35:56,840
Master Klao.

575
00:35:56,880 --> 00:35:58,040
- Master.
- Master Klao.

576
00:35:58,080 --> 00:35:58,800
Master Klao!

577
00:35:58,840 --> 00:35:59,800
- What?!
- Master!

578
00:36:00,280 --> 00:36:01,120
Master Klao.

579
00:36:02,120 --> 00:36:03,120
- Whoa! What?!
- Master Klao!

580
00:36:03,760 --> 00:36:04,720
- Master Klao.
- Master.

581
00:36:05,000 --> 00:36:06,570
- Master Klao!
- Gosh! Who are you?

582
00:36:07,640 --> 00:36:09,200
- Ow! That hurt!
- Master.

583
00:36:09,920 --> 00:36:11,200
His Excellency and the Lord

584
00:36:11,240 --> 00:36:13,720
have commanded us
to search for you these several days.

585
00:36:14,560 --> 00:36:16,560
What circumstances led you to these woods?

586
00:36:17,200 --> 00:36:17,920
Huh?!

587
00:36:25,320 --> 00:36:26,120
Master?

588
00:36:26,560 --> 00:36:27,480
What the hell?

589
00:36:39,480 --> 00:36:41,280
- Bastard!
- You son of a rogue!

590
00:36:42,960 --> 00:36:44,960
Father and son alike, wretched both!

591
00:36:46,360 --> 00:36:48,240
- Scum!
- The likes of you shall never prosper, Klao!

592
00:36:49,800 --> 00:36:52,720
The likes of you shall never prosper, Klao!

593
00:36:52,760 --> 00:36:54,120
Does your head hurt, Master Klao?

594
00:36:54,340 --> 00:36:56,800
Everyone! Escort him back
to His Excellency's estate.

595
00:36:57,440 --> 00:36:58,320
Master Klao!

596
00:36:58,800 --> 00:36:59,960
My Master!

597
00:37:00,080 --> 00:37:00,720
Master Klao!

598
00:37:00,760 --> 00:37:01,760
Master!

599
00:37:01,880 --> 00:37:03,480
My Master!

600
00:37:03,520 --> 00:37:04,520
- What a comfort!
- Whoa!

601
00:37:04,560 --> 00:37:05,960
Master, you are still alive?

602
00:37:06,520 --> 00:37:07,680
- How are you, Master?
- Hey!

603
00:37:09,600 --> 00:37:12,520
Who are you guys?

604
00:37:13,280 --> 00:37:14,400
And I'm...

605
00:37:16,480 --> 00:37:17,680
I'm not dreaming, am I?

606
00:37:20,040 --> 00:37:21,240
I beg your pardon?

607
00:37:25,120 --> 00:37:26,120
You've got it all wrong.

608
00:37:26,320 --> 00:37:27,320
I'm not Klao.

609
00:37:27,600 --> 00:37:28,680
Oh, Master.

610
00:37:28,720 --> 00:37:30,560
You still jest at a time such as this?

611
00:37:30,600 --> 00:37:32,560
This suggests that you are well.

612
00:37:32,600 --> 00:37:33,400
Is it not so?

613
00:37:34,360 --> 00:37:35,080
You...

614
00:37:42,280 --> 00:37:44,400
You guys are filming a period piece,
aren't you?

615
00:37:44,720 --> 00:37:47,640
Since when has my mom
let people film a play in her orchard?

616
00:37:49,920 --> 00:37:50,800
Film...

617
00:37:53,960 --> 00:37:55,120
A play?

618
00:37:56,840 --> 00:37:57,840
A play...

619
00:37:58,200 --> 00:37:58,920
You...

620
00:37:59,160 --> 00:38:01,120
What are you doing? Filming content?

621
00:38:04,360 --> 00:38:05,320
Master Klao...

622
00:38:09,840 --> 00:38:10,560
Wait...

623
00:38:11,240 --> 00:38:12,440
This is different from last night.

624
00:38:13,360 --> 00:38:14,440
What is this place?

625
00:38:23,320 --> 00:38:24,400
Last night,

626
00:38:24,440 --> 00:38:25,840
I was drinking.

627
00:38:27,960 --> 00:38:29,560
After that, I left the house.

628
00:38:31,280 --> 00:38:32,880
And then, the star fell!

629
00:38:34,840 --> 00:38:36,320
Then I ended up here.

630
00:38:38,500 --> 00:38:39,580
What's next?

631
00:38:40,480 --> 00:38:42,880
God! I was too drunk to remember anything!

632
00:38:43,360 --> 00:38:44,880
I too have been pondering

633
00:38:44,920 --> 00:38:46,760
the circumstances that brought you here.

634
00:38:47,120 --> 00:38:48,000
My Lord...

635
00:38:48,160 --> 00:38:49,120
My Lord.

636
00:39:20,680 --> 00:39:21,680
Who's that?

637
00:39:22,040 --> 00:39:23,040
He looks so familiar.

638
00:39:23,420 --> 00:39:24,500
A celebrity?

639
00:39:26,520 --> 00:39:27,520
How is that?

640
00:39:28,480 --> 00:39:29,600
Will you now tell me?

641
00:39:32,640 --> 00:39:33,360
Uh...

642
00:39:34,280 --> 00:39:36,200
I think you've got it all wrong.

643
00:39:36,720 --> 00:39:38,200
I'm not an actor.

644
00:39:38,440 --> 00:39:42,120
I'm Ms. Nahathai's son,

645
00:39:43,120 --> 00:39:45,520
from the nearby mango orchard.

646
00:39:45,760 --> 00:39:48,400
Last night, I must've gotten pretty drunk,

647
00:39:48,440 --> 00:39:51,160
wandered around, and ended up here.

648
00:39:52,200 --> 00:39:54,400
That said,
I won't trouble you any further.

649
00:39:54,800 --> 00:39:55,680
Take care, guys.

650
00:39:56,400 --> 00:39:57,280
Seize him!

651
00:39:57,320 --> 00:39:58,760
- Do not let him stray from our sight.
- What the hell?

652
00:40:00,240 --> 00:40:01,240
Hey, let go of me!

653
00:40:01,560 --> 00:40:02,240
You...

654
00:40:03,200 --> 00:40:04,280
This course of action...

655
00:40:04,640 --> 00:40:06,400
I could sue you for this!

656
00:40:10,360 --> 00:40:11,800
Master Klao! Master!

657
00:40:11,920 --> 00:40:13,240
Master! Master Klao!

658
00:40:13,280 --> 00:40:14,120
Master Klao!!

659
00:40:19,440 --> 00:40:20,440
My Lord!

660
00:40:20,760 --> 00:40:22,520
I beg you, my Lord,
please spare him the cane.

661
00:40:22,680 --> 00:40:24,000
The fault is mine alone.

662
00:40:24,120 --> 00:40:27,440
You entrusted Master Klao to me,

663
00:40:27,680 --> 00:40:29,080
yet I have failed you
by permitting him to indulge in spirits.

664
00:40:29,120 --> 00:40:29,920
Enough!

665
00:40:31,160 --> 00:40:32,800
No one shall be punished.

666
00:40:33,680 --> 00:40:35,400
Attend to your master at once,

667
00:40:35,920 --> 00:40:37,240
and bring him back to the small manor.

668
00:40:38,960 --> 00:40:40,240
Shall we not go to
His Excellency's estate?

669
00:40:40,960 --> 00:40:41,920
Not at this moment.

670
00:40:42,180 --> 00:40:43,260
Is it not evident

671
00:40:43,440 --> 00:40:45,640
that your master is troubled in mind?

672
00:40:46,100 --> 00:40:48,100
I wish to spare my parents from distress.

673
00:40:49,520 --> 00:40:50,320
Yes, my Lord.

674
00:40:51,280 --> 00:40:52,760
Waste no time.

675
00:40:53,320 --> 00:40:54,600
Find Klao at once.

676
00:40:55,400 --> 00:40:56,880
I shall follow shortly after.

677
00:40:58,040 --> 00:40:59,040
Yes, my Lord.

678
00:41:00,120 --> 00:41:01,220
Master Klao!

679
00:41:02,000 --> 00:41:02,920
Master Klao! Master!

680
00:41:02,960 --> 00:41:03,920
Master!

681
00:41:03,960 --> 00:41:05,480
Master Klao! Master!

682
00:41:05,520 --> 00:41:07,200
- Master!
- Master Klao!!

683
00:41:09,120 --> 00:41:10,320
Let go of me!

684
00:41:11,000 --> 00:41:12,080
- Master...
- Let me go!

685
00:41:12,360 --> 00:41:13,840
Let go!!

686
00:41:14,200 --> 00:41:15,080
Ow!

687
00:41:15,440 --> 00:41:17,240
I told you to let go of me! Come on!

688
00:41:18,080 --> 00:41:19,920
You've got the wrong person!

689
00:41:19,960 --> 00:41:21,080
Please, Master.

690
00:41:23,680 --> 00:41:25,000
Master, please.

691
00:41:25,040 --> 00:41:26,600
I'll sue! I'll sue!!

692
00:41:26,920 --> 00:41:27,760
My phone.

693
00:41:28,600 --> 00:41:30,400
You even took my phone from me?!

694
00:41:31,480 --> 00:41:32,480
- Master Klao.
- Gosh!!

695
00:41:33,040 --> 00:41:34,280
Not going anywhere!

696
00:41:37,240 --> 00:41:38,840
Let me go!!

697
00:41:39,280 --> 00:41:40,360
Let go!

698
00:41:40,880 --> 00:41:42,600
Help! Somebody, help!

699
00:41:43,600 --> 00:41:44,240
This way, Master.

700
00:41:44,280 --> 00:41:45,160
Gentle, please!

701
00:42:01,120 --> 00:42:02,280
Where am I now?

702
00:42:03,280 --> 00:42:05,800
Lord Phop has arranged
these quarters for your comfort.

703
00:42:06,760 --> 00:42:07,560
Lord?

704
00:42:08,800 --> 00:42:11,080
You mean the guy
with the scary-looking face?

705
00:42:12,600 --> 00:42:14,400
Please cease this mockery, Master Klao.

706
00:42:14,800 --> 00:42:17,240
My heart grows uneasy.

707
00:42:17,380 --> 00:42:18,960
You guys need to stop playing games.

708
00:42:20,280 --> 00:42:21,660
I'm not entertained by this.

709
00:42:22,000 --> 00:42:23,000
It actually hurt.

710
00:42:25,240 --> 00:42:27,560
And you dragged me
to a cabin in the middle of nowhere, too.

711
00:42:31,240 --> 00:42:33,360
"Cabin in the middle of nowhere"?

712
00:42:35,040 --> 00:42:37,120
This is kidnapping.

713
00:42:37,880 --> 00:42:39,640
I'll take this matter all the way.

714
00:42:40,100 --> 00:42:42,100
Also, tell the 'Lord,' or whoever he is,

715
00:42:42,600 --> 00:42:44,080
to be ready to face me in court.

716
00:42:52,520 --> 00:42:53,520
Master.

717
00:42:54,200 --> 00:42:56,240
How may I, Chuay,

718
00:42:56,760 --> 00:42:57,920
be of service to you?

719
00:42:58,200 --> 00:42:59,200
Your name's Chuay?

720
00:43:00,760 --> 00:43:01,760
Master...

721
00:43:03,160 --> 00:43:04,760
Even I, you...

722
00:43:11,360 --> 00:43:12,200
It's hot in here.

723
00:43:12,440 --> 00:43:14,040
Can you turn on the air conditioner, Chuay?

724
00:43:15,200 --> 00:43:15,880
Hm?

725
00:43:16,600 --> 00:43:17,360
The A/C.

726
00:43:20,240 --> 00:43:21,160
Turn on...

727
00:43:21,440 --> 00:43:22,280
the A...

728
00:43:26,580 --> 00:43:27,760
Don't tell me there's no A/C here.

729
00:43:29,640 --> 00:43:31,720
Grant this humble servant
your pardon, Master.

730
00:43:33,980 --> 00:43:35,720
Stop calling me Klao already.

731
00:43:35,960 --> 00:43:37,240
My name is not Klao!

732
00:43:37,920 --> 00:43:38,840
Master Klao...

733
00:43:39,880 --> 00:43:40,800
What a waste of time.

734
00:43:42,240 --> 00:43:43,120
No, Master!

735
00:43:43,320 --> 00:43:45,600
It is at the Lord's request
that you seek repose here.

736
00:43:45,640 --> 00:43:46,800
Should you leave,

737
00:43:46,840 --> 00:43:48,520
I shall surely receive a harsh caning.

738
00:43:49,960 --> 00:43:52,080
Can you stop playing
the character for a second?

739
00:43:54,120 --> 00:43:55,200
Playing the character?

740
00:43:57,220 --> 00:43:58,400
I fear I lack the talent.

741
00:43:58,440 --> 00:43:59,440
I have not mastered the art.

742
00:44:00,360 --> 00:44:01,800
You keep up your character so well.

743
00:44:02,400 --> 00:44:04,040
Where did you learn to act?

744
00:44:04,080 --> 00:44:06,320
You are well aware that

745
00:44:06,480 --> 00:44:07,720
I am no master of Farangi speech.

746
00:44:09,480 --> 00:44:10,480
What speech?

747
00:44:10,920 --> 00:44:12,040
"Farangi," Master.

748
00:44:13,160 --> 00:44:14,880
"Farangi"?

749
00:44:15,560 --> 00:44:16,680
Like, French?

750
00:44:17,020 --> 00:44:18,280
I was speaking English.

751
00:44:19,360 --> 00:44:21,160
"Fa-ran-gi," Master.

752
00:44:22,240 --> 00:44:23,520
Who cares.

753
00:44:24,200 --> 00:44:25,200
Listen.

754
00:44:25,380 --> 00:44:27,480
I don't know what you're trying to do,

755
00:44:27,520 --> 00:44:30,240
maybe make a screenplay,
kidnap me for ransom,

756
00:44:30,720 --> 00:44:32,120
or something,

757
00:44:32,680 --> 00:44:34,520
but you've got the wrong guy.

758
00:44:34,760 --> 00:44:36,200
My name is not Klao.

759
00:44:36,440 --> 00:44:38,040
It's 'Nakun.'

760
00:44:38,680 --> 00:44:40,840
Also, I'm useless to you.

761
00:44:41,040 --> 00:44:43,480
My mom definitely doesn't have
money for a ransom.

762
00:44:49,760 --> 00:44:50,560
Chuay.

763
00:44:51,760 --> 00:44:52,960
You look like a good person.

764
00:44:55,560 --> 00:44:58,360
Can you please...let me go?

765
00:45:00,160 --> 00:45:01,240
I won't snitch.

766
00:45:14,040 --> 00:45:15,240
Master! Wait!

767
00:45:22,120 --> 00:45:23,520
Where do you wander to now, Klao?

768
00:45:25,200 --> 00:45:26,440
I'm getting out of here.

769
00:45:27,160 --> 00:45:27,920
Move.

770
00:45:28,960 --> 00:45:30,160
You are attired somewhat oddly.

771
00:45:32,040 --> 00:45:33,160
Hey, what are you doing?

772
00:45:33,800 --> 00:45:34,680
Stop it.

773
00:45:35,200 --> 00:45:36,400
The butterfly-shaped mark of birth.

774
00:45:37,200 --> 00:45:38,800
There is no mistaking you, Klao.

775
00:45:41,040 --> 00:45:42,040
Butterfly-shaped?

776
00:45:42,240 --> 00:45:44,160
It's shaped like
the northern region of Thailand.

777
00:45:44,480 --> 00:45:45,880
Have your wits forsaken you?

778
00:45:46,080 --> 00:45:48,120
Is it overindulgence
that clouds your words?

779
00:45:48,600 --> 00:45:50,000
I'm the one speaking coherently.

780
00:45:51,720 --> 00:45:53,200
Sure, I had
a little too much to drink last night,

781
00:45:53,240 --> 00:45:54,840
but I wasn't out cold or anything.

782
00:45:58,040 --> 00:45:59,520
Have you guys lost your minds,

783
00:45:59,840 --> 00:46:01,280
claiming that I'm Klao?

784
00:46:01,400 --> 00:46:03,480
Why, then, did you claim you were not Klao?

785
00:46:06,040 --> 00:46:07,360
Nobody here gets it.

786
00:46:07,560 --> 00:46:09,240
I told you I'm not Klao!

787
00:46:28,720 --> 00:46:30,360
Gosh, what the hell is going on?!

788
00:46:32,080 --> 00:46:32,800
Master Klao!

789
00:46:35,720 --> 00:46:36,600
Master!!

790
00:46:36,640 --> 00:46:37,560
Master Klao.

791
00:46:39,360 --> 00:46:40,440
Master Klao!

792
00:46:43,920 --> 00:46:44,840
Where am I?

793
00:46:44,880 --> 00:46:46,400
How the hell did I end up here?

794
00:46:46,440 --> 00:46:48,080
What happened to me?!

795
00:46:48,640 --> 00:46:49,520
Master Klao! Stop!

796
00:46:49,560 --> 00:46:50,280
Master.

797
00:46:50,560 --> 00:46:52,200
I beg you, Master.

798
00:46:53,640 --> 00:46:54,800
Wait, Master!

799
00:46:54,840 --> 00:46:55,680
Master Klao!

800
00:47:04,160 --> 00:47:05,360
Gosh! Still following me?

801
00:47:06,040 --> 00:47:06,840
Master Klao!

802
00:47:08,880 --> 00:47:10,720
I'm probably in a film shoot
for a period piece.

803
00:47:11,040 --> 00:47:13,120
The extras are rehearsing
for their scenes, aren't they?

804
00:47:18,920 --> 00:47:19,760
Master!

805
00:47:20,120 --> 00:47:21,360
Please wait, Master.

806
00:47:21,880 --> 00:47:22,920
Master Klao.

807
00:47:22,960 --> 00:47:24,040
How is this even played?

808
00:47:25,800 --> 00:47:26,640
Master Klao!

809
00:47:26,680 --> 00:47:27,680
Hey, move!

810
00:47:28,200 --> 00:47:29,720
Out of the way!

811
00:47:30,200 --> 00:47:31,400
Move!

812
00:47:32,240 --> 00:47:33,080
Master...

813
00:47:33,200 --> 00:47:34,760
Awesome job on the props.

814
00:47:35,000 --> 00:47:36,280
So realistic.

815
00:47:36,560 --> 00:47:38,560
What company is behind this?!

816
00:47:39,320 --> 00:47:40,120
Master Klao.

817
00:47:44,560 --> 00:47:45,560
Be wary, Master!

818
00:47:46,200 --> 00:47:47,120
Make way, if you please.

819
00:47:47,160 --> 00:47:48,080
Make way, I beg you!

820
00:47:48,800 --> 00:47:50,200
Please wait, Master.

821
00:47:52,080 --> 00:47:53,440
Yes, this is it!

822
00:47:53,480 --> 00:47:57,200
Many period pieces were filmed here!

823
00:48:00,640 --> 00:48:01,840
Where are all the crew members?

824
00:48:02,080 --> 00:48:03,400
Help me!

825
00:48:04,600 --> 00:48:05,680
Master Klao!

826
00:48:06,360 --> 00:48:07,560
Do wait, Master!

827
00:48:09,880 --> 00:48:11,200
Do not go there!

828
00:48:11,240 --> 00:48:12,640
My feet can go no further!

829
00:48:13,600 --> 00:48:15,240
My poor feet can bear no more!

830
00:48:15,280 --> 00:48:16,880
- Master Klao!
- This place is not to be entered, Master!

831
00:48:18,360 --> 00:48:19,800
This quarter must not be entered!

832
00:48:19,840 --> 00:48:20,680
Master.

833
00:48:20,880 --> 00:48:22,160
I beg of you, Master! Stop!

834
00:48:26,440 --> 00:48:27,440
Excuse me.

835
00:48:27,920 --> 00:48:29,920
You guys are working on a series, correct?

836
00:48:30,280 --> 00:48:31,120
Well...

837
00:48:31,960 --> 00:48:33,840
I'm not here to interrupt you, but...

838
00:48:35,680 --> 00:48:40,280
Can anyone tell me
how to get out of this filming location?

839
00:48:45,840 --> 00:48:46,840
Dear Klao.

840
00:48:47,820 --> 00:48:48,960
Where have you wandered off to?

841
00:48:53,320 --> 00:48:54,320
Dearest Klao.

842
00:48:56,400 --> 00:48:57,520
So you have returned.

843
00:48:57,800 --> 00:48:59,400
Come, let us eat together.

844
00:49:02,840 --> 00:49:04,240
No, thank you.

845
00:49:05,800 --> 00:49:06,880
My Prayong.

846
00:49:07,600 --> 00:49:08,680
Yes, my love?

847
00:49:10,060 --> 00:49:11,920
Has dearest Klao lost his wits?

848
00:49:15,320 --> 00:49:17,120
Oh, good heavens.

849
00:49:17,640 --> 00:49:19,640
Indeed, a most unfortunate fate...

850
00:49:23,560 --> 00:49:24,360
Klao.

851
00:49:24,760 --> 00:49:25,560
Klao!

852
00:49:26,680 --> 00:49:27,480
Klao!!

853
00:49:28,160 --> 00:49:29,280
- Let us settle this matter.
- Gosh!

854
00:49:29,320 --> 00:49:30,520
Stop chasing me!

855
00:49:38,240 --> 00:49:39,240
Oh, heavens!
I nearly tumbled down the stairs.

856
00:49:39,280 --> 00:49:40,160
I'm really sorry!

857
00:49:41,560 --> 00:49:43,080
I nearly went down with him.

858
00:49:58,400 --> 00:50:00,640
If this isn't a film set,
then where the hell am I?

859
00:50:00,760 --> 00:50:02,680
Scratch traveling back in time
off the list.

860
00:50:02,720 --> 00:50:03,720
It's impossible.

861
00:50:04,400 --> 00:50:06,640
And who the hell is that Lord Paddle Phop?

862
00:50:07,000 --> 00:50:08,000
It's not coming to me.

863
00:50:08,260 --> 00:50:09,800
But he looked at me

864
00:50:09,960 --> 00:50:11,880
like we'd known each other forever.

865
00:50:13,760 --> 00:50:14,960
Master!

866
00:50:15,680 --> 00:50:17,000
Master Klao!

867
00:50:17,800 --> 00:50:19,800
Pray, stop running.

868
00:50:33,520 --> 00:50:34,520
Master Klao!!

869
00:50:35,600 --> 00:50:37,280
At last, you are within my grasp!

870
00:50:37,320 --> 00:50:38,680
Remain still, Master.

871
00:50:39,360 --> 00:50:41,120
Be still, I beg you.

872
00:50:41,960 --> 00:50:43,840
Master Klao, cease this.

873
00:50:45,120 --> 00:50:46,200
Pray, remain still!

874
00:50:55,080 --> 00:50:56,400
Stop chasing me already!

875
00:50:57,760 --> 00:50:58,640
Help me, please.

876
00:50:58,680 --> 00:50:59,680
Somebody, help.

877
00:51:00,760 --> 00:51:01,520
Klao!

878
00:51:02,440 --> 00:51:04,800
Anyone but him!

879
00:51:06,600 --> 00:51:08,080
Let us speak and be understood.

880
00:51:08,760 --> 00:51:09,980
I refuse!

881
00:51:10,480 --> 00:51:11,520
Oh, Master!

882
00:51:11,720 --> 00:51:13,120
Are you well?

883
00:51:20,560 --> 00:51:21,720
Sis, move!

884
00:51:24,120 --> 00:51:25,720
I can do this all day.

885
00:51:30,440 --> 00:51:31,560
Gosh! My intrusive thoughts!

886
00:51:36,080 --> 00:51:37,400
Everyone's acting so well.

887
00:51:38,120 --> 00:51:39,760
Artistic integrity is unreal.

888
00:51:40,400 --> 00:51:42,400
I don't think this is a film set.

889
00:51:47,280 --> 00:51:48,280
Shit!

890
00:51:49,340 --> 00:51:50,880
What is the matter, Master Klao?

891
00:51:54,800 --> 00:51:55,680
It hurts,

892
00:51:56,040 --> 00:51:57,120
but I'm not waking up.

893
00:51:57,720 --> 00:51:59,380
This isn't a dream.

894
00:52:03,440 --> 00:52:05,640
I don't think scammers
pull off stuff this fancy, either.

895
00:52:05,800 --> 00:52:07,360
Where am I even?

896
00:52:07,400 --> 00:52:08,400
A mysterious village

897
00:52:08,800 --> 00:52:10,320
and weird cultists?
Like the ones in the movies?

898
00:52:16,240 --> 00:52:17,240
Master Klao!

899
00:52:17,640 --> 00:52:18,360
Master!

900
00:52:18,720 --> 00:52:19,560
Cease this, Master.

901
00:52:19,600 --> 00:52:20,280
Master!

902
00:52:21,120 --> 00:52:21,720
A rooster?!

903
00:52:21,760 --> 00:52:23,120
- Master Klao!
- I am utterly weary, Master.

904
00:52:24,000 --> 00:52:24,720
Master Klao!

905
00:52:26,800 --> 00:52:27,800
Master, where are you going?!

906
00:52:32,720 --> 00:52:33,800
- Master, I beg you!
- Ah!

907
00:52:34,240 --> 00:52:34,880
Master Klao!!

908
00:52:34,920 --> 00:52:36,040
I do fight back, alright?!

909
00:52:39,480 --> 00:52:41,120
Master, compose yourself!

910
00:52:41,960 --> 00:52:43,240
Be wary!

911
00:52:43,280 --> 00:52:44,280
I beg you, Master!

912
00:52:48,440 --> 00:52:49,520
- Don't come any closer!
- Master, do cease this.

913
00:52:54,040 --> 00:52:55,040
Ah! What the hell are you?!

914
00:52:56,680 --> 00:52:57,600
Do not go, I beg you!

915
00:52:59,400 --> 00:53:00,520
- Master Klao?
- After him!

916
00:53:00,560 --> 00:53:01,520
Help me!

917
00:53:01,560 --> 00:53:02,960
- Master!
- Master Klao...

918
00:53:15,280 --> 00:53:16,320
Hey, stop!

919
00:53:21,320 --> 00:53:22,080
Hey!

920
00:53:22,120 --> 00:53:23,080
Don't come any closer!

921
00:53:23,120 --> 00:53:24,600
I'll curse you...

922
00:53:24,640 --> 00:53:25,880
I'll curse you all!

923
00:53:25,920 --> 00:53:26,920
What do I do now?

924
00:53:27,120 --> 00:53:28,920
Espresso Petroleum!

925
00:53:28,960 --> 00:53:30,560
A perfect name for a drink, isn't it?!

926
00:53:51,320 --> 00:53:53,040
Have I really traveled back in time?

927
00:53:53,760 --> 00:53:55,080
How did I even do it?

928
00:53:56,320 --> 00:53:59,200
When we think of traveling through time,

929
00:54:02,300 --> 00:54:05,360
we usually imagine it happening
with a time machine,

930
00:54:05,600 --> 00:54:08,400
magic, some kind of sorcery,

931
00:54:09,400 --> 00:54:11,560
or a portal.

932
00:54:11,760 --> 00:54:16,120
But sometimes, drifting off to sleep,

933
00:54:16,640 --> 00:54:18,200
passing out,

934
00:54:18,780 --> 00:54:20,840
or being knocked out by an accident

935
00:54:20,880 --> 00:54:23,760
can make someone travel back in time.

936
00:54:24,080 --> 00:54:26,120
When it comes to traveling back in time,

937
00:54:26,160 --> 00:54:29,760
death is considered the starting point.

938
00:54:30,280 --> 00:54:34,000
It's about dying
and traveling to a different realm,

939
00:54:34,420 --> 00:54:36,800
then being reincarnated as someone else.

940
00:54:38,480 --> 00:54:39,680
A portal?

941
00:54:39,920 --> 00:54:40,720
Ah!

942
00:54:41,360 --> 00:54:42,440
It's like in video games.

943
00:54:42,480 --> 00:54:44,600
If we die,
we'd start over from the beginning.

944
00:54:45,120 --> 00:54:46,760
I must've blacked out

945
00:54:46,800 --> 00:54:48,000
and ended up here.

946
00:54:48,600 --> 00:54:49,800
If I die now,

947
00:54:50,000 --> 00:54:51,600
do I go back to the present day?

948
00:54:53,320 --> 00:54:54,200
My Lord...

949
00:54:55,000 --> 00:54:56,080
It has been far too long.

950
00:54:57,800 --> 00:54:58,640
At your word, shall we...

951
00:56:01,800 --> 00:56:03,160
This way, Curer.

952
00:56:06,160 --> 00:56:07,040
Thee?!

953
00:56:07,280 --> 00:56:08,200
Klao.

954
00:56:08,440 --> 00:56:09,000
Pun!

955
00:56:09,040 --> 00:56:10,280
Yes. I'm safe now.

956
00:56:10,320 --> 00:56:11,240
Klao.

957
00:56:11,400 --> 00:56:13,080
Jom's words were true.
You have lost your wits.

958
00:56:13,480 --> 00:56:14,400
You...

959
00:56:14,440 --> 00:56:17,600
Regarding Klao's affairs, your heart
is more troubled than by your own.

960
00:56:17,720 --> 00:56:19,200
That deadpan lord.

961
00:56:19,320 --> 00:56:20,240
Is he taken?

962
00:56:20,280 --> 00:56:23,840
The Lord usually takes no regard
for the welfare of others.

963
00:56:24,400 --> 00:56:26,040
His concern is reserved solely for...

964
00:56:27,120 --> 00:56:28,680
you, Master Klao.

965
00:56:35,600 --> 00:56:40,640
♫Seeing you feels like destiny come true♫

966
00:56:40,680 --> 00:56:45,680
♫All that I dream and long for leads to you♫

967
00:56:45,720 --> 00:56:50,360
♫Fate isn't chance, but something meant to be♫

968
00:56:50,400 --> 00:56:55,640
♫Thank you for giving love its meaning to me♫

969
00:56:55,680 --> 00:57:00,640
♫Seeing you now is more than fantasy♫

970
00:57:00,680 --> 00:57:05,480
♫Every second I give you faithfully♫

971
00:57:05,680 --> 00:57:11,480
♫As time goes on, no matter where we are♫

972
00:57:11,600 --> 00:57:19,520
♫My heart is yours, no matter near or far♫

